article.description: — Chris Fields Jr. had 19 points in Norfolk State's 68-58 victory over Coppin State on Saturday night.
article.headline: Norfolk State defeats Coppin State 68-58
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- — Chris Fields Jr. had 19 points in Norfolk State's 68-58 victory over Coppin State on Saturday night. Fields also contributed five rebounds for the Spartans (13-8, 3-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Tyrel Bladen scored 11 points and added six rebounds. Christian Ings had 10 points and shot 4 of 9 from the field and 2 for 3 from the line. The Eagles (2-16, 1-3) were led by Ryan Archey and Khali Horton, who each posted 15 points. In addition, Greg Spurlock finished with eight points and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
